definition.value: The decapeptide gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) is the master hormone regulating reproduction. GnRH is released from some 1000 neurons within the hypothalamus in a pulsatile manner. Hypothalamic GnRH gene expression occurs intermittently (in a pulsatile fashion). The primary target of hypothalamic GnRH is the anterior pituitary gonadotrope, which responds to stimulation by increasing the synthesis and secretion of the gonadotropins luteinzing hormone (LH) and follicle stimulating hormone (FSH), which in turn regulate gonadal development and function.

https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0500052 (Retinopathy of prematurity stage 3)  ; abnormality of the eye

value.value: 未熟児網膜症ステージ3

Neovaskularizace se hromadí na okraji vaskularizované sítnice a zasahuje do sklivce (také se nazývá extraretinální fibrózní proliferace). V případě zóny 2 a zóny 3 může mít tvar klobásy. V případě posteriornějšího onemocnění Zóny 1 se stadium 3 může jevit jako přímé rozšíření normálních sítnicových cév, které se však tangenciálně rozšiřují přes avaskulární sítnici.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: The neovascularization accumulates at the edge of the vascularized retina and extends into the vitreous (also called extra retinal fibrosis proliferation). In cases of Zone 2 and Zone 3, this may be sausage shaped. In more posterior Zone 1 disease, the stage 3 can appear as a direct extension of the normal retinal vessels but extending tangentially over the avascular retina.

value.value: Neovaskülarizasyon vaskülarize retinanın kenarında birikir ve vitreusa uzanır (ekstraretinal fibroz proliferasyonu da denir). zone 2 ve zone 3 vakalarında bu, sosis şeklinde olabilir. Daha posterior tutulumu olan zone 1 hastalığında, evre 3 avasküler retina üzerinde teğet olarak uzanan normal retina damarlarının doğrudan bir uzantısı olarak görülebilir

https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0500062 (Retinopathy of prematurity plus)  ; abnormality of the eye

value.value: 早产儿视网膜病附加病变

Posterior retinal damarların arterioler bükülmesi ve venöz dilatasyonu ve sonra iris vasküler tıkanmasını, zayıf pupiller dilatasyonunu (rijit pupil) ve vitröz bulanıklığı içerecek şekilde ciddiyette artış olabilir. Bu tanım daha sonra ilaveten, eğer gözün en az iki kadranında yeterli vasküler dilatasyon ve bükülme mevcut olduğunda plus hastalığı tanısı yapılabildiği klinik araştırmalarda geliştirilmiştir

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Venous dilatation and arteriolar tortuosity of the posterior retinal vessels and may later increase in severity to include iris vascular engorgement, poor pupillary dilatation (rigid pupil), and vitreous haze. This definition has been further refined in the later clinical trials in which the diagnosis of plus disease could be made if sufficient vascular dilatation and tortuosity are present in at least 2 quadrants of the eye.

Venózní dilatace a arteriolární tortuozita zadních sítnicových cév a později se může stupňovat až k vaskulárnímu překrvení duhovky, špatné dilataci zornic (rigidní zornice) a sklivcovému zákalu. Tato definice byla dále upřesněna v pozdějších klinických studiích, ve kterých bylo možné stanovit diagnózu plus onemocnění, pokud je přítomna dostatečná vaskulární dilatace a tortuozita alespoň ve dvou kvadrantech oka.
